description.narrative: By 2021, central and decentralized entities are better equipped to produce, analyse, disseminate and use compelling data appropriately, to inform, implement, monitor and evaluate inclusive social policies and programmes for children., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews, Evaluation, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Reducing Child Poverty, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021 Children's rights are better documented, and the Government uses these records to inform, cost and implement inclusive social policies.

description.narrative: Afin d’informer le Programme de Coopération 2023-2027, une analyse des risques affectant les enfants, (CRIA), a été réalisée avec la participation des enfants et jeunes vulnérables et quatre évaluations et études relatives aux resultats clés pour les enfants (KRC) sont disponibles, dépassant le nombre de trois initialement prévu. La planification et le suivi des programmes ont été renforcés : Les plans de travail roulants et les revues conjointes avec les partenaires ont des cadres de resultats plut robustes, permettant de mieux informer les ajustements des interventions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
